, 11, 309, 1355, 257, 707, 857, 544, 294, 4319, 5717, 364, 560, 6206, 320, 5513, 50688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 45, "seek": 19530, "start": 201.78, "end": 202.78, "text": " in market structure.", "tokens": [50688, 294, 2142, 3877, 13, 50738], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 46, "seek": 19530, "start": 202.78, "end": 209.46, "text": " It just means that there's likely a downside draw or an upside draw intraday by saying", "tokens": [50738, 467, 445, 1355, 300, 456, 311, 3700, 257, 25060, 2642, 420, 364, 14119, 2642, 560, 6206, 320, 538, 1566, 51072], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 47, "seek": 19530, "start": 209.46, "end": 210.46, "text": " the term shift.", "tokens": [51072, 264, 1433, 5513, 13, 51122], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 48, "seek": 19530, "start": 210.46, "end": 211.46, "text": " OK.", "tokens": [51122, 2264, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 49, "seek": 19530, "start": 211.46, "end": 213.14000000000001, "text": " So there's a little bit of semantics there.", "tokens": [51172, 407, 456, 311, 257, 707, 857, 295, 4361, 45298, 456, 13, 51256], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 50, "seek": 19530, "start": 213.14000000000001, "end": 214.14000000000001, "text": " All right.", "tokens": [51256, 1057, 558, 13, 51306], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 51, "seek": 19530, "start": 214.14000000000001, "end": 221.86, "text": " So we have both of these areas here and here where there would be a likelihood of a market", "tokens": [51306, 407, 321, 362, 1293, 295, 613, 3179, 510, 293, 510, 689, 456, 576, 312, 257, 22119, 295, 257, 2142, 51692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 52, "seek": 19530, "start": 221.86, "end": 223.62, "text": " structure shift.", "tokens": [51692, 3877, 5513, 13, 51780], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1328659516114455, "compression_ratio": 1.76036866359447, "no_speech_prob": 0.23240701854228973}, {"id": 53, "seek": 22362, "start": 223.62, "end": 227.78, "text": " Up here, we look for a fake run above here.", "tokens": [50364, 5858, 510, 11, 321, 574, 337, 257, 7592, 1190, 3673, 510, 13, 50572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12852076121738978, "compression_ratio": 1.7552447552447552, "no_speech_prob": 0.19067861139774323}, {"id": 54, "seek": 22362, "start": 227.78, "end": 231.26, "text": " So that fake run above, how do we know it's going to be a market structure shift that's", "tokens": [50572, 407, 300, 7592, 1190, 3673, 11, 577, 360, 321, 458, 309, 311, 516, 281, 312, 257, 2142, 3877, 5513, 300, 311, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12852076121738978, "compression_ratio": 1.7552447552447552, "no_speech_prob": 0.19067861139774323}, {"id": 55, "seek": 22362, "start": 231.26, "end": 232.26, "text": " bearish?", "tokens": [50746, 6155, 742, 30, 50796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12852076121738978, "compression_ratio": 1.7552447552447552, "no_speech_prob": 0.19067861139774323}, {"id": 56, "seek": 22362, "start": 232.26, "end": 236.62, "text": " I get that question a lot, even from mentorship students.", "tokens": [50796, 286, 483, 300, 1168, 257, 688, 11, 754, 490, 40422, 1731, 13, 51014]